      "The electric flux \\( \\Phi \\) through an area element \\( \\Delta S \\) is given by \\( \\Phi = \\frac{q \\Delta S}{\\epsilon_0 r^2} \\), where \\( \\epsilon_0 \\) is the permittivity of free space, \\( r \\) is the distance from the charge to the area element, and the unit vector \\( \\hat{r} \\) is along the radius vector from the charge to the area element.",
