    "steps": [
      "The electromagnetic field acts as a mediator in the interaction between two charges. When one charge (q1) is accelerated, it produces electromagnetic waves that propagate outward at the speed of light. These waves carry energy and momentum, and when they reach the second charge (q2), they exert a force on it. This field concept elegantly accounts for the time delay between the motion of q1 and the force experienced by q2, providing a causal link between the two events."
    ],
